\int_o^\pi x\cos^4x\,dx
x=\pi/2-y
\int_0^\pi xf(\sin x )dx=\frac \pi2\int_0^\pi f(\sin x )dx
I=\int_{o}^{\pi} x\cos^4x=\frac \pi2\int_0^\pi \cos^4xdx=\pi\int_0^{\pi/2} \cos^4xdx
I=\pi\int_0^{\pi/2} \cos^4xdx=\pi\int_0^{\pi/2} \sin^4xdx
2I=\pi\int_0^{\pi/2} (\sin^4x+\cos^4x)dx=\frac \pi4\int_0^{\pi/2} (\cos(4 x)+3) dx= \frac{3 \pi^2}{8}
I= \frac{3 \pi^2}{16}.
I=\int_0^\pi x\cos^4x\,dx
I=\int_0^\pi (\pi-x)\cos^4(\pi-x)\,dx
\cos(\pi-x)=-\cos x
I=\pi\int_0^\pi \cos^4x\,dx -I 
2I=\pi\int_0^\pi \cos^4x\,dx 
f(x)=\cos^4x,f(-x)=\{\cos(-x)\}^4=\cos^4x=f(x)
\int_0^\pi \cos^4x\,dx =2\int_0^{\frac\pi 2}\cos^4x\,dx
\cos^4 x={1\over16}(e^{ix}+e^{-ix})={1\over8}\bigl(3+4\cos(2x)+\cos(4x)\bigr)
\eqalign{J&:=\int_0^\pi  x\cos^4 x\ dx \cr &={1\over8}\Bigl(x(3x+2\sin(2x)+{1\over4}\sin(4x)\Bigr)\biggr|_0^\pi -{1\over8}\int_0^\pi \bigl(3x+2\sin(2x)+{1\over4}\sin(4x)\bigr)\ dx\ .\cr}
J={1\over8}\cdot 3\pi^2-{1\over8}\int_0^\pi 3x\ dx= {3\pi^2\over16}\ .
\,\cos^4x\,
\cos^4x=\cos^2x(1-\sin^2x)=\cos^2x-\cos^2x\sin^2x
\int\cos^2x\,dx=\frac{x+\cos x\sin x}{2}\,.\,.\,.\,.\,(\text{Hint: use, for example, }\,\,\cos 2x=2\cos^2x-1):
\int\cos^2x\sin^2x\,dx=-\frac{\cos^3x\sin x}{3}+\frac{1}{3}\int\cos^4x\,dx\,.
\,K:=\int \cos^4x\,dx
K=\frac{1}{2}(x+\cos x\sin x)+\frac{1}{3}(\cos^3x\sin x)-\frac{1}{3}K\Longrightarrow
K=\left.\frac{3}{8}\left(x+\cos x\sin x\right)+\frac{1}{4}\left(\cos^3x\sin x\right)\right|_0^\pi=\frac{3\pi}{8}
\,\displaystyle{I=\frac{\pi}{2}K}\,
